HEADWORD: paleencephalon
<hw>paleencephalon</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>The more primitive parts of
the brain phylogenetically; it includes most structures other than the
cerebral cortex.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> paleoencephalon, palaeoencephalon.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

